	  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

		<introduction>
			<para>
				The Double Agent API reproduces and extends the features of the Microsoft<superscript>®</superscript>
				Agent API.
			</para>
			<para>
				It consists of two main components:
			</para>
			<list class="bullet">
				<listItem>
					<para>
						A <token>COMname</token> (<token>COM</token>)
						<newTerm>Server</newTerm> that allows multiple applications, called <newTerm>clients</newTerm>
						or <newTerm>client applications</newTerm>,
						to access its animation, input, and output services at
						the same time. A client can be any application that connects to the Double Agent
						server's <token>COM</token> interfaces.
					</para>
					<para>
						As a <token>COM</token> server, the Double Agent server automatically
						starts only when a client application uses its <token>COM</token> interfaces
						and connects to it. It remains running until all clients close their connections.
						When no connected clients remain, the Double Agent server automatically shuts down.
					</para>
				</listItem>
				<listItem>
					<para>
						An <token>ActiveXCtl</token>
						that makes it easy to access Double Agent's services from programming languages
						that support the <token>ActiveXInt</token>.
					</para>
					<para>
						The control can be connected to the server, allowing Agent characters to be shared
						among multiple applications. It can also run <link xlink:href="e084673a-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#standalone">standalone</link>,
						providing Agent characters that are private to a specific application.
						This is a new feature of Double Agent that is not supported by <token>MsAgent</token>.
					</para>
					<para>
						The control also allows Double Agent to provide it's character animation services
						<link xlink:href="e084673a-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#contained">contained</link> within a <newTerm>child</newTerm>
						window of a <newTerm>client application</newTerm>'s window. This is a new feature of Double
						Agent that is not supported by <token>MsAgent</token>.
					</para>
				</listItem>
			</list>
			<para>
				See the Double Agent <link xlink:href="e0846750-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">Server</link> and <link xlink:href="e0846730-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">Control</link> interfaces for more information on the specific API.
			</para>
			<para>
				In addition to supporting stand-alone programs written for <token>Windows</token>,
				Double Agent can be scripted to support <link xlink:href="e0846736-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">Web pages</link>,
				provided that the browser supports <token>COMauto</token> or the <token>ActiveXInt</token>.
				<token>MSIE</token> and other browsers include
				support for <token>ActiveXCtls</token> as well as scripting languages that you can use
				to program Double Agent.
			</para>
		</introduction>
